nderestimated - initial masses for the most luminous stars in the Arches cluster approach 200 M. according to contemporary stellar and photometric results. The potential for stars greatly exceeding 150 M. within metal-poor galaxies suggests that such pair-instability supernovae could occur within the local universe, as has been claimed for SN 2007bi. {\textcopyright} 2010 The Authors. Journal compilation {\textcopyright} 2010 RAS.},
