rom the blue-dominated peak Ly{\$}\backslashalpha{\$} emission (with a blue-to-red peak line ratio {\$}I{\_}{\{}\backslashrm blue{\}}/I{\_}{\{}\backslashrm red{\}} \backslashsimeq 3.7{\$}) and redshifted ISM absorption ({\$}\backslashsimeq 100{\$} km s{\$}{\^{}}{\{}-1{\}}{\$}). Our results suggest that J1316+2614 is undergoing a gas compaction event, possibly representing a short-lived phase in the evolution of massive and compact galaxies, where strong gas inflows have triggered an extreme star formation episode and nearly {\$}100\backslash{\%}{\$} LyC photons are escaping.},
