 equivalent width can only reduce the observed W(H$\beta$). From our direct probe of the massive star content we conclude that there is at present no evidence for systematic variations of the upper mass cut-off of the IMF in metal-rich environments, in contrast to some claims based on indirect nebular diagnostics.},
